{"title": "In Chancery (Forsyte Saga Vol. 2)", "description": "'The Forsyte Saga' is the story of a wealthy London family stretching from the eighteen-eighties until the nineteen-twenties. <i>In Chancery</i> is the second book in the saga. Five years have passed since Irene left Soames and the death of Bosinney. Old Jolyon meets Irene and is enchanted by her. At his death he leaves her a legacy sufficient for her to live an independent life in Paris.<br /><br />\nSoames who is desperate for a son, attempts to effect a rapprochement but is rejected by her. Meanwhile Young Jolyon, now a widower,who is Irene\u2019s trustee falls in love with her<br /><br />\nSoames suspects Young Jolyon and Irene of adultery and sues for divorce. His action is successful. Young Jolyon and Irene marry. She bears him a son, John. Soames remarries. His wife Annette bears him a daughter, Fleur. (Summary by Andy Minter)", "duration": 48862, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2340", "name": "John Galsworthy"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt12/In_Chancery_1110.jpg", "copyright_year": "1918", "genres": ["General Fiction", "Romance", "Sagas"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Andy Minter (1934-2017)"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Gesine"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "0:1 Indian Summer of a Forsyte 1", "readers": [705], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_chancery_0709_librivox/inchancery_01_galsworthy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3144}, {"section": 2, "title": "0:2 Indian Summer of a Forsyte 2", "readers": [705], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_chancery_0709_librivox/inchancery_02_galsworthy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1177}, {"section": 3, "title": "0:3 Indian Summer of a Forsyte 3", "readers": [705], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_chancery_0709_librivox/inchancery_03_galsworthy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1476}, {"section": 4, "title": "0: